They eat when all people had their diet, to make sure that everyone have their food and food is not in shortage then old monks can eat. If the food is not enough then the high level monk(s) should care the others that the all monks are equal.
And the delicious food can't be served only or intentionally for high-leveled monks. The good food should be eaten by the normal monks first.




IDK what the people do in nowadays but what I said is from ancient sutra. The original vinaya or discipline is sooo good. So much caring for people :D I think the modern people might don't even know it.
The full discipline is 2 systems. The one is the monks can eat meat and another one is can't. This two system is specially designed by buddha himself to create self-contradiction. In a way it's a kind of prove that vinaya is not very important because it have 2 systems that have even opposite thing.
The most important teaching is never exist contradiction they always consist.
Vinaya / discipline is just a thing to teach people how to live in their life. e.g how to get along with others.
